---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About | Jeff Conners" description="About the artist and process behind the collection.">
  <section class="hero flow-section flow-section--first reveal">
    <p class="section-label">About</p>
    <h1>
      Seeing differently,
      <span class="accent">painting honestly.</span>
    </h1>
    <p>
      Jeff Conners works with contrast, line tension, and layered value. His colorblind
      perception leads to unexpected combinations — what others might avoid, he leans into.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="two-col flow-section reveal">
    <article class="panel">
      <p class="section-label">Process</p>
      <p>
        Work starts with shape studies and tonal sketches, then moves into acrylic and mixed-media sessions.
        Final pieces balance strong geometry with organic texture.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="panel">
      <p class="section-label">Vision</p>
      <p>
        The goal is simple: build room for the art itself. Minimal interface, large format imagery, and
        clear metadata keep focus where it belongs.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</Layout>
